      "title": "Form IX Verbs for Colors and Defects",
      "titleArabic": "باب اِفْعَلَّ للألوان والعيوب",
      "content": [
        "Form IX (اِفْعَلَّ) is exclusively used for colors and physical defects. It indicates becoming or acquiring a color or defect."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: اِفْعَلَّ with doubled final radical",
        "Colors: اِحْمَرَّ (became red), اِخْضَرَّ (became green)",
        "Defects: اِعْوَرَّ (became one-eyed), اِعْرَجَّ (became lame)",
        "All Form IX verbs are intransitive"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِحْمَرَّ وَجْهُهُ خَجَلًا", "english": "His face became red from embarrassment" },
        { "arabic": "اِصْفَرَّتِ الْأَوْرَاقُ", "english": "The leaves became yellow" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Advanced Accusative of Purpose",
      "titleArabic": "المفعول لأجله المتقدم",
      "content": [
        "The maf'ūl lahu must meet specific conditions: it must be a maṣdar, indicate reason, share the same subject and time as the main verb."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Must be a maṣdar indicating reason",
        "Must share subject with main verb",
        "Must be contemporaneous with the action",
        "If conditions not met, use لِ + noun"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "قُمْتُ إِجْلَالًا لِلْمُعَلِّمِ", "english": "I stood out of respect for the teacher" },
        { "arabic": "سَافَرَ طَلَبًا لِلرِّزْقِ", "english": "He traveled seeking provision" }
      ]
    }
